{
  "text": "A combination of factors including increased activity of the renin-angiotensin system, sodium, and water retention and increased activity of the sympathetic system contribute to the development of hypertension in creatinine value was used to estimate GFR using the modification of diet in renal disease (MDRD) (4 variable) formula which has been previously validated among Nigerians. [CITATION_1] Patients were grouped according to eGFR into two groups: Those with eGFR \u226560 ml/min (mild CKD) and those with eGFR <60 ml/min (moderate to severe CKD).",
